{
 "name": "RPlog_Burning_Sands",
 "title": "Burning Sands",
 "summary": "On a rocky overlook above Mos Eisley, the Trandoshan hunter Nachkt'lyysk lies in wait for a New Republic diplomatic convoy carrying Ambassador Ambrosia Delgard, planning to use his own transport as a weapon for the Imperial bounty. As the caravan crosses the dunes, the hunter's ship swoops in and shatters it with turret fire, destroying the escort speeders one by one while the marines die defending their charge. Ambrosia survives the carnage but is horrifically burned when her bodyguard Merk is blown apart and his molten remains fuse to her back; cornered and in shock, she surrenders the blaster she had crawled for. Nachkt descends to claim her, and her supposed rescuer, the Corellian holo-producer Ewan Dain, leaps from the ship's turret only to realize, to his horror, that he has helped ambush her. Aboard the freighter Maiden's Prayer, Nachkt stuns Ambrosia unconscious for treatment and reveals his true game to Dain: he intends to use her as a political trade piece to win Imperial credibility so he can find the abducted Wookiees. Dain, anguished and threatening, ultimately backs down, agreeing to go along with the hunter's plan while vowing terrible retribution if any harm comes to her.",
